figgy.title: Try generating pmtiles without guessing max zoom after failure

comments.body:
@hackartisan The program we use to generate the pmtiles file has an option to automatically set a max zoom level on the dataset. Otherwise you have to set it manually. The command fails when there is only one feature (point in most cases) in the original data. E.g. a dataset of the port locations in Singapore, but there is only one. This setting requires more than one point and the command fails. The PR adds a fallback that reruns the command without this option. There really isn’t anything to take a screenshot of. Derivative generation fails.

The option is “-zg”: https://github.com/felt/tippecanoe#linear-features-world-railroads-visible-at-all-zoom-levels
Thanks for the extra context that's helpful!
